==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grizzly
<hw>Griz"zly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Somewhat gray;
grizzled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old squirrels that turn <qex>grizzly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Grizzly bear</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a large
and ferocious bear (<spn>Ursus horribilis</spn>) of Western North
America and the Rocky Mountains. It is remarkable for the great length
of its claws.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grizzly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Grizzly
<hw>Griz"zly</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Grizzlies</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A grizzly
bear. See under <er>Grizzly</er>, <pos>a.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>In hydraulic mining, gratings used
to catch and throw out large stones from the sluices.</def>
<mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark> <rj><au>Raymond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>groan</ent>⟦br⟧
